      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="use-qr-code-to-log-in" data-step-uuid="8339b4ed-1782-411e-88f5-837e436be01b">
    <h2 id="use-qr-code-to-log-in" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Use QR Code to Log In</h2>
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_d1db1dfb-21d2-459e-80e6-0bf6bc9a8961" class="text-block-content">
    <p>There’s a very simple way to log in to the Canvas Parent app. In the web version of Canvas, if you click the Account link in the Global Navigation menu, you’ll see a QR for Mobile Login link. After opening the Canvas Parent app on your mobile device, scan that code. You will be instantly logged-in, without having to worry about connecting to your school and retyping your information.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/t5/Observer-Guide/How-do-I-view-a-QR-code-to-log-in-to-the-Canvas-mobile-apps-as/ta-p/545" target="_blank">How do I view a QR code to log in to the Canvas mobile apps as an observer?</a></li>
<li><a href="/t5/Canvas-Parent-iOS-Guide/How-do-I-log-in-to-the-Canvas-Parent-app-on-my-iOS-device-with-a/ta-p/2072" target="_blank">How do I log in to the Canvas Parent app on my iOS device with a QR code?</a></li>
<li><a href="/t5/Canvas-Parent-Android-Guide/How-do-I-log-in-to-the-Parent-app-on-my-Android-Device-with-a-QR/ta-p/2048" target="_blank">How do I log in to the Parent app on my Android Device with a QR code? </a></li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>
 
